      \field{abstract}{Robotic process automation ({RPA}) is a technology for centralized automation of business processes. {RPA} automates user interaction with graphical user interfaces, whereby it promises efficiency gains and a reduction of human negligence during process execution. To harness these benefits, organizations face the challenge of classifying process activities as viable automation candidates for {RPA}. Therefore, this work aims to support practitioners in evaluating {RPA} automation candidates. We design a framework that consists of thirteen criteria grouped into five perspectives which offer different evaluation aspects. These criteria leverage a profound understanding of the process step. We demonstrate and evaluate the framework by applying it to a real-life data set.}
